03/04/2003
LONDON, United Kingdom -- Bosnia and Herzegovina staged a major upset in the latest round of European championship soccer qualifiers on Wednesday (2 April) when it beat Denmark in Copenhagen by 2-1. 
In other games, the Bulgaria-Estonia match in Tallinn ended in a 0-0 draw, but Bulgaria continued to lead its group. 
Croatia moved to second place in the same group with a 2-0 victory over Andorra. 
Albania held Ireland to a scoreless draw in Tirana. 
Greece beat Northern Ireland in Belfast by 2-0 and Turkey lost by 0-2 to England in Sunderland. 
In a friendly game in Lausanne, Portugal beat Macedonia by 1-0. 
(AP, AFP - 02/04/03)
